Product Bakes
Moister Cakes

Juan M. Gonzalez-Sanz of the Pillsbury Co. (200 S. 6th St.,
Minneapolis, MN 55402-1464; Tel: 612/330-4741) invented a low-fat
spreadable composition that can be used with baked foods or alone,
as a frosting.   Shortening, starch, a hydrocolloid, an emulsifier,
and a sweetener make up the product.  The starch has a hydrophilic
starch component and a modified hydrophobic starch component.

When used as a frosting, the low-fat composition exhibits enhanced
adhesion.  When used in baked foods, such as cakes, rolls, breads,
biscuits, and pastries, the product increases the moistness. U.S.
Patent 5,439,697 was issued to Pillsbury for this invention.



