KANE'S BEVERAGE WEEK via NewsNet
January 8, 1996

Beer Production Rose in August


     U.S. production of beer in August was 18,819,013 barrels, up
1.5% from the like 1994 month, according to the Bureau of Alcohol,
Tobacco and Firearms.
     Taxable removals in August fell to 16,844,658 barrels, a 1%
decline from the like year-earlier month.




