January 8, 1996   Number 3457

JEAN-PIERRE ROSSO

When JEAN-PIERRE ROSSO took over heavy-equipment manufacturer Case in 1994,
it hadn't turned much of a profit in years. Cost-cutting by parent Tenneco
stopped the bleeding, but there was no strategy. He redesigned Case's
outdated construction- and agricultural-equipment lines and focused on
Europe. The payoff? Earnings in 1995 should double, to $250 million, on an
11% hike in sales, to $4.8 billion.

