ANDREW S. GROVE made 1995 the year Intel moved beyond merely being the

ANDREW S. GROVE made 1995 the year Intel moved beyond merely being the
world's biggest chipmaker to being the biggest force in the entire computer
industry. Grove, 59, pushed into motherboards, logic chipsets, and even
entire computers. Intel's next targets include engineering workstations and
large servers. Its 1995 sales are expected to be up more than 40%, to $15
billion.

