JOHN J. MACK

In one of Wall Street's best years ever, Morgan Stanley Group President
JOHN J. MACK had a nice one of his own. Mack, 51, forcefully integrated
independent departments. It worked. The firm's stock rose 43%, and its
earnings soared 73%. Under Mack, Morgan became the only foreign investment
bank allowed to do business inside China.

