CASEY G. COWELL

He's chairman of the hottest U.S. modem manufacturer. Thanks to the
explosion of computer networks, CASEY G. COWELL's U.S. Robotics saw
revenues explode to $889 million in 1995, up from $378.6 million in '94.
Cowell, 43, built new plants and designed faster modems. He also bid for
bankrupt Hayes Microcomputer Products, once the country's largest modem
maker. Cowell is shooting for a $5 billion company by 2000.

