LEWIS E. PLATT

How do you make a huge company grow 20% a year? In 1995, Hewlett-Packard
CEO LEWIS E. PLATT showed 'em how again. Sales are up 26%, to $31.5
billion; profits are up 52%, to $2.4 billion. Platt, 54, tapped RICHARD E.
BELLUZZO, 42, to merge the retail-minded PC and printer division with the
old Big Iron business. Platt believes corporations want one-stop shopping
for information technology, and he's giving it to them.

