The production index edged up during the week ended Dec. 16. Before
calculation of the four-week moving average, the index rose to 129.8, from
128.5. Increases in the seasonally adjusted output of autos, trucks, and
electric power led the advance.

The leading index was up slightly in the latest week. The unaveraged index
dropped to 262.4, from 263.1 in the previous week. Higher stock prices and
lower bond yields are signaling solid economic growth ahead.

