     Adele D. Hazel, 60, a newly licensed real estate agent in

     Adele D. Hazel, 60, a newly licensed real estate agent in
Annandale, VA, has established a fund to which real estate
agents, brokers, and others can donate money to help house the
homeless.  She has pledged to donate to the fund all commissions
she receives from selling houses.  Hazel joined Pyon Realty in
Annandale in March and has already persuaded two agents there to
donate part of their commissions to the fund.  "There's been more
talk than action on solving the plight of the homeless," Hazel
said.



