COMMUNITY FOUNDATIONS

     The Columbus Foundation has released its spring newsletter.
Highlights: assets of more than $150 million and distributions of
$12.8 million in 1989 were the foundation's highest ever; the
recent election of Eldon W. Ward, president of the E.E. Ward
Moving and Storage Company, as chairman of the foundation's
Governing Committee; and the receipt in 1989 of nearly $15.2
million in contributions.  The foundation's deadlines for its
various program areas are as follows: education, November 1990;
health, January 1991; social services, February 1991; arts and
conservation, April 1991; social services (second round), July
1991; and civic affairs, September 1991.  Contact the foundation
at 1234 E. Broad Street, Columbus, OH 43205, (614) 251-4000.



