TOY TESTING: Besides testing electrically-operated toys, UL can classify

TOY TESTING: Besides testing electrically-operated toys, UL can classify wide
range of toys to CPSC, ASTM and European norm standards.  UL's 1994 pact with
Hong Kong's toy testing agency HKSTC allows UL to review CPSC testing and
issue the UL mark for toys that comply with standards.  But firms must
participate in UL's worldwide follow-up program.



