RESIDENTIAL EARTHQUAKE INSURANCE AVAILABILITY

By Jean K. Rosales, Economics Division.  6 pages.  Although
residential earthquake insurance is available in every state,
concerns have been expressed about the overall availability of such
insurance.  Problems with insurance availability can be divided into
categories based on the type of damages anticipated.  This, in turn,
facilitates the development and implementation of government remedies
to insurance availability problems.  Order No. 92-248 E.

The full report, as described above and authored by the Congressional
Research Service, costs $47 from Penny Hill Press, 6440 Wiscasset
Road, Bethesda, MD  20816, 301-229-8229.



