EDUCATION RESEARCH AMENDMENTS:  A SUMMARY OF H.R. 4014 AND COMPARISON
WITH CURRENT LAW

By Paul M. Irwin, Education and Public Welfare Division.  16 pages.
This report analyzes H.R. 4014, the Educational Research,
Development, and Dissemination Excellence Act, a proposal to
reauthorize education research activities through fiscal year 1966.
The bill authorizes a $144.5 million appropriation for fiscal year
1993, double the current fiscal year 1992 appropriation; 4 national
education research institutes; a national education dissemination
system; and a National Education Research Library.  Order No. 92-282
EPW.

