MOTOR FUEL MARKETING COMPETITION AND H.R. 2966

By Bernard A. Gelb, Economics Division.  9 pages.  This report first
describes the structure and patterns of motor fuel marketing, and the
events that have buffeted them.  Then, the key provisions of H.R.
2966, the Petroleum Marketing Competition Enhancement Act, are
presented and analyzed with respect to their likely effects on motor
fuel marketing.  The report does not attempt to resolve conflicting
assertions by proponents and opponents of the bill regarding market
behavior.  Order No. 92-238 E.

The full report, as described above and authored by the Congressional
Research Service, costs $47 from Penny Hill Press, 6440 Wiscasset
Road, Bethesda, MD  20816, 301-229-8229.



