CONGRESSIONAL RESEARCH REPORT via NewsNet
JUNE, 1992

BANK MERGERS AND INTERSTATE BANKING:  POLICY ISSUES

By William Jackson, Economics Division.  25 pages.  To some
observers, the very survival of the banking industry as we know it
appears threatened.  Its falling market shares and profitability may
suggest that industry consolidation is necessary to eliminate excess
capacity; some believe through nationwide banking involving
acquisitions across state lines.  But would the result be consistent
with financial competition?  This report analyzes the economic
relationships involved, and presents policy options for Congress to
deal with them.  Order No. 92-305 E.

The full report, as described above and authored by the Congressional
Research Service, costs $47 from Penny Hill Press, 6440 Wiscasset
Road, Bethesda, MD  20816, 301-229-8229.



