ISRAEL'S ELECTION, 1992:  ISSUE BRIEF

By Clyde R. Mark, Foreign Affairs and National Defense Division.
Israel is scheduled to hold parliamentary elections on June 23, 1992.
Issues in the campaign may include electoral reform, unemployment,
economic reforms, housing, treatment of recently arrived immigrants
from the former Soviet Union, settlements in the occupied
territories, and, in particular, the Arab-Israeli peace process begun
in Madrid in October 1991 and continuing in Washington.  Order No.
IB92060.

