BASIC QUESTIONS ON U.S. CITIZENSHIP AND NATURALIZATION

By Larry M. Eig, American Law Division.  6 pages.  Answers these
questions:  Who is a United States citizen at birth?  How does one
become a naturalized citizen?  Must citizens take loyalty oaths?
What is the required period of residency prior to being eligible for
citizenship?  Is a citizenship revocable?  If so, under what
circumstances?  Finally, are there provisions for dual citizenship?
If so, under what circumstances?  Order No. 92-246 A.

