THE EUROPEAN DEFENSE INDUSTRY:  RESPONSES TO GLOBAL CHANGE AND
EUROPEAN INTEGRATION

By Theodor W. Galdi, Foreign Affairs and National Defense Division.
20 pages.  There are four main sections to this report.  The first
briefly discusses the current structure and near-term outlook for
West European defense producers in light of moves toward European
integration and the declining worldwide demand for arms.  The second
section examines the major arms exports by France, the United
Kingdom, and the Federal Republic of Germany over the last decade.
Potential future export possibilities are also discussed in this
section.  The third section sets out the activities and goals of the
European Commission, the Independent European Program Group, and the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization intended to harmonize and
rationalize the defense trade.  The final section sets out U.S.
policy responses and issues for consideration by Congress.  Order No.
92-284 F.

