Thomas says: antitrust


At the end of 1995, FTC:WATCH asked the House of Representatives computer
system how many bills involving antitrust issues had been introduced during
the year.  Answer:  96.

Here they are.  Those items having the largest concentration of the relevant
term ("antitrust") appear first in the list.

1 .  Professional  Baseball Antitrust  Reform Act  of 1995  (Introduced in the
House) [H.R.386]

2 .  To provide that professional baseball teams, and leagues composed of such
teams, shall be subject to the antitrust laws.  (Introduced in the House)
[H.R.749]

