January 17, 1996

Schnuck supermarket divestiture


What goes around may come around, sort of.

When Schnuck Markets, Inc.  acquired supermarkets owned by National Holdings,
Inc.  the FTC charged the acquisition would harm supermarket competition in
the St.  Louis, Missouri-area.  To settle those charges, Schnuck has proposed
divesting 23 stores in that area to a newly formed company, Family Company of
America, whose senior management "consists largely of former senior managers
of the National Holdings, Inc.  supermarket chain."

If the divestitures are allowed, Family would become the third-largest
competitor in the area, Schnuck said in asking for approval of the
divestitures.

